“Well what to say, I love making something out of nothing” Goodbye my beloved @thejojobaby 💖✨💋You embraced me when I moved to chicago in 2009. I was a closeted queer stripper hustling in the clubs at night to pay my way through college and survive the winters. Meeting you was pure magic. It felt like falling down the rabbit hole, like Alice in your wonderland ✨✨✨ You showed me what it truly means to be yourself, fully realized living  your fantasy. You and sissy were the first people I came out to and you loved me like family. You gave me my first pasties and popped me on stage giving me permission to live, with freedom and love. You have blessed so many people with your gifts, art and spirit. When all the club kidz were at our lowest, freezing in Chicago, you lifted us up with fantasy and the power of building a LQQK. I know so many of us would not be where we are today without our JOJO BABY. Your artistry and influence will echo through our spirits and in our work for lifetimes to come. I miss you my dear friend. 💔 🌈 💋 🧚🏻‍♀️ #jojobaby

Pride is more than just a celebration of love and equality - it’s a reminder of the courage, resilience, and solidarity of the queer community. As a queer person, I am grateful for the love and support of my chosen family, and for the activists and advocates who fought for our rights and freedoms. But I also know that there is still work to be done, to protect and amplify the voices of those who are still marginalized, discriminated against, and silenced. Today, let’s celebrate how far we’ve come, and commit ourselves to the work that lies ahead. Happy Pride, my beautiful family! 🏳️‍🌈🌈❤️

“You are my rock, you are my silver lining”-Gmama 💋Remembering my incredible Gmama, who made countless sacrifices for our family. She sold her home to support us, becoming a second mother to me. From driving me to school every day to attending my burlesque shows, she was always there. She beat breast cancer, survived a heart attack, and held on until the very end, our hands intertwined until the last breath. Her unwavering will to thrive was unmatched. She embraced adventure, flying hot air balloons, riding Harley’s, and even getting tattoos in her 50s. She encouraged my love for animals and psychic phenomena. With her silly and fun-loving spirit, she was the life of every party. Despite her battle with dementia, my mother provided and protected her. It’s a cruel disease, but her love for life never wavered. It’s so important that we stand by our elders and take care of one another. So many people are forgotten and abandoned in their last hours, but the love of my small but mighty family of women never wavered. Love is most valuable thing in the universe. As we say goodbye, I know it’s just the beginning of a new journey. Until we meet again on the other side, I love you forever. 💞 🐢 🐈 🐕 🐩 🐖 🐓 💋

In honor of #dwarfismawarenessmonth my princess @misstosh highlighted our journey from friendship to an otherworldly love that i never knew i would have the chance to experience. The first time I really fell hard for Tosh was when she was in a floor length, emerald green gown & opted out of sitting in a normal chair, & instead chose to sit on my step stool beside me while I was busy working. I fell so hard ! 🤤

Having a disability in today’s society is challenging. We are in an in-between phase of more acceptance & education, while others are still white-knuckling misogyny, racism, & ableism. I’ve had people in past relationship&dating who were too afraid to introduce me to family, or friends, while simultaneously telling me they love me. It saddens me so many people with dwarfism experience this, but all I’ve ever focused on having in my life is community, and living in truth—so i remained single for many many years until i took a chance on pursuing someone who I admired, and felt supported and celebrated my humor, my body, my DJ’ing, tarot reading *and* MC’ing skills! When the MPEG, writer’s and actor’s strikes happened, they affected everyone—especially people with disabilities working in the city. I needed to find ways keep my accessible housing. Tosh was there booking me and helping me refine my performance skills, side hustles, and helping keep an accessible roof over my head before we ever considered dating. 

Experiencing Tosh’s friendship and love has been so freeing and we make our own traditions. I feel so cared for, physically and emotionally. She believes in the career I’ve built, she treats my loyal friendships like gold, and she always reminds me I am her Kueen. I love you princess, and I love building our fantasy life together. By our first anniversary we’ve been in 6 different countries and I honestly wouldn’t have left America if it wasn’t for you. I thank Goddess I have you to call and FaceTime from 15 hours and 6,000 miles ahead everyday while I’m away. Thank you for being My rock, My sun, My moon, My stars! My Toshy!!! 
 (She arranged for this couples photoshoot as a surprise before I left for China!🥲)
